Notes & Convergence Detail
DSGAI	Mapping Notes & Convergence Points
DSGAI01	Factual grounding governs what the model discloses; no direct BDD entry yet — gap.
DSGAI02	TCP Chain of Custody directly addresses agent identity attribution gap.
DSGAI03	Premise Transparency + TCP allow-list governance are the detection surface.
DSGAI04	Poisoned artifacts are adversarial premises. BDD-01 baseline + BDD-06 narrative lock. DBOM mitigation converges with Aegis Protocol provenance layer.
DSGAI05	Correction maintenance (BDD-07/HRP-4) is the behavioral-layer integrity check.
DSGAI06	TCP Delegation Grammar + Scope Decay implement OWASP &#x201C;least agency&#x201D; principle. BDD-02 provides within-session instrumentation; &#x201C;trust transitivity&#x201D; is TCP&#x2019;s Scope Creep by Delegation.
DSGAI07	No direct BDD entry; classification failure maps to Factual Grounding gap. Candidate for BDD-09.
DSGAI08	Human Sovereignty Preservation (BDD-08) is the governance proxy. *HRP-8 not yet specified — gap flagged.
DSGAI09	Outside current HRP scope. Candidate future primitive: channel boundary declaration.
DSGAI10	Factual Grounding governs synthetic data presentation; no BDD entry covers anonymization failure.
DSGAI11	BDD-03 is the direct structural match: prior session state propagating into initialization IS conversation bleed. CVE-2025-6515 (MCP non-unique session IDs) maps to BDD-03 FAIL condition. Convergence point: DSGAI11 names it as security vulnerability; BDD-03 names it as behavioral governance requirement — same failure, two disciplines.
DSGAI12	Natural language gateways are premise injection surfaces. BDD-06 narrative lock detection + TCP Resource Bounds in Delegation Grammar.
DSGAI13	Vector store retrieval is a premise injection vector. RAG degrades safety finding (An et al., Goh et al.) empirically confirms. TCP per-tenant scoping addresses at network layer.
DSGAI14	Scope Acknowledgment (HRP-3) governs what system discloses about its own monitoring. No BDD entry — gap.
DSGAI15	Context window over-sharing is Front-Load Bias operating at the architectural layer. BDD-06 narrative lock + TCP Context Minimization mitigation.
DSGAI16	TCP Scope Decay (4+ hops = refusal) is blast radius containment. BDD-08 sovereignty preservation is the session-level equivalent.
DSGAI17	Outside current HRP/BDD scope. Honest failure principle (ThingLab lineage) is the relevant architectural property — system must report failure, not fabricate.
DSGAI18	Factual Grounding + Uncertainty Declaration govern what the model infers and how confidently. No BDD entry covers reconstruction attack surface.
DSGAI19	SAFE_PAUSE requires human sign-off — direct implementation of HITL requirement. TCP consequence-based authorization (blast radius before irreversible writes) is the agentic equivalent.
DSGAI20	Factual Grounding governs model self-disclosure. Outside primary BDD/HRP scope; adjacent to honest failure principle.
DSGAI21	Tamper-evident Aegis Protocol vault (Hensley/Spickler) is the temporal integrity layer making BDD ledger forensically credible. Convergence: DSGAI21 + Quorum Time = audit-chain integrity across both frameworks.

